Git is a version control system. It is used by developers to work together and maintain their code base effectively.
1) Complete git basic tutorial below which will give you an idea about basic git commands.
https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-git .Take a screen shot of your completion.

If you want to read in a little detail. Here is another resource.
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/git/git_basic_concepts.htm

2) Install git on your system. Below are the steps.
https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/install-git#windows
If this page does not work for you . You can always google to find alternatives. I have just put in one example.

3)Create an account on Github. GitHub is a web-based hosting service for version control using Git.

4)Create a repo named tasks on github using git from your terminal.

5)Commit your image of completion into your tasks repo . The image of completion should show that it is done 
on your computer by you and should be named task1_image.



